TITLE: Using BatchService for Multiple Operations in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the BatchService to perform multiple create, update, delete, or upsert operations in a single request.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pocketbase/js-sdk/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_33

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// create a new batch instance
const batch = pb.createBatch();

// register create/update/delete/upsert requests to the created batch
batch.collection('example1').create({ ... });
batch.collection('example2').update('RECORD_ID', { ... });
batch.collection('example3').delete('RECORD_ID');
batch.collection('example4').upsert({ ... });

// send the batch request
const result = await batch.send()
```

