TITLE: Sending Batch/Transactional Requests with PocketBase JS SDK
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use the batch API to send multiple operations (create, update, delete, upsert) in a single transaction. This feature was introduced in version 0.22.0 and works with PocketBase v0.23.0+.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pocketbase/js-sdk/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const batch = pb.createBatch();

batch.collection("example1").create({ ... });
batch.collection("example2").update("RECORD_ID", { ... });
batch.collection("example3").delete("RECORD_ID");
batch.collection("example4").upsert({ ... });

const result = await batch.send();
```

