TITLE: Demonstrating Auto Cancellation in PocketBase JavaScript SDK
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the auto cancellation feature of the PocketBase SDK. It shows how duplicate requests are automatically cancelled, and how to modify this behavior using the requestKey parameter or by globally disabling auto cancellation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pocketbase/js-sdk/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20) // cancelled
pb.collection('example').getList(2, 20) // cancelled
pb.collection('example').getList(3, 20) // executed
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20);                        // cancelled
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20);                        // executed
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20, { requestKey: "test" }) // cancelled
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20, { requestKey: "test" }) // executed
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20, { requestKey: null })   // executed
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20, { requestKey: null })   // executed

// globally disable auto cancellation
pb.autoCancellation(false);

pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20); // executed
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20); // executed
pb.collection('example').getList(1, 20); // executed
```

